          "body": "Verse 17 is the most beautiful evangelistic invitation in Scripture: *The Spirit and the bride say, Come. And let the one who hears say, Come. And let the one who is thirsty come; let the one who wishes take the water of life without cost.* Three concentric circles widen the call: the Spirit and the bride together (divine + ecclesial unity in mission); the one who hears (the convert becomes evangelist immediately); the one who is thirsty (anyone with felt need). The water is *dorean* — free, without cost — echoing Isaiah 55:1. At the end of a book full of judgment, plagues, and the lake of fire, the canon's final invitation is grace. As Spurgeon observed, the gospel net is cast even at the threshold of the consummation; the door is open until the Bridegroom arrives."
